{
  "stem": "21731.2",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Mokshany.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But 'Mokrawy' is, is-- in, in English, it would be 'dampness.' Mokrawy.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "In Polish, it means something, yes, is damp.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So Mokshany must have been a place where it was very damp around-- perhaps they were damp.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I don't know.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I never was there.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, I had no white wedding dress because I found it was very funny, those white wedding dresses.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I could not-- I was still very practical also.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I had really not enough money to have a dress and never wear it again.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But  that was against my [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] upbringing.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And so I decided, together with my, my sister-- well, my sister-in-law, my future sister-in-law, Lusia, who was very, very well-dressed always and very-- [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] knew everything about what has one to wear, and how it should look, and all the makeup which she wanted me to wear and I never wore.",
      "word_count": 55
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But anyway, coming back to the dress, I didn't want a white dress.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I wanted a dress which I can wear later.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And so my dressmaker [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] bought from-- I don't know, from Paris, I suppose-- a very beautiful, light-blue silk.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And it was a, a dress which I  could wear later and wore later quite often.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And with this dress, I had a coat, navy blue-- not really navy, I would say it is perhaps a French blue now-- which was lined with this silk, a hat to match, which I hated.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I always hated hats.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And, well, this hat was very simple because at the wedding, I had a white veil, which my aunt forgot to bring to the wedding.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "But she had-- somebody brought it quick and the hat as well.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
